# AWS Auto-Remediation Bot (S3 Public Access)

This project automatically detects when an S3 bucket becomes public and instantly remediates it by applying secure Block Public Access settings.

It represents real-world cloud security engineering using:
- AWS EventBridge
- AWS Lambda
- AWS IAM (least privilege)
- CloudTrail events
- Security automation patterns

This is exactly the type of automation used by real cloud security teams to enforce guardrails and prevent misconfiguration.

---

# ðŸ”¹ What This Project Does

1. Detects when an S3 bucket becomes public.
2. Automatically applies secure Block Public Access settings.
3. Logs all actions to CloudWatch.
4. (Optional) Sends notifications to a security channel.

This fits directly into:
- Zero Trust  
- Cloud Governance  
- Incident Response  
- IAM & Security  
- Automation Playbooks  

